    %div.section#introduction
      %h3 Introduction
      %p This is the central place for hyphenation patterns in T<sub class="tex">E</sub>X.  They are all bundled in a single package called hyph-utf8.
      %ul
        %li
          %a{href: "http://tug.org/mailman/listinfo/tex-hyphen"} tex-hyphen mailing list
        %li
          %a{href: "https://github.com/hyphenation/tex-hyphen"} tex-hyphen source repository
        %li
          %a{href: "http://mirror.ctan.org/language/"} language directory on CTAN

      %h4 For pattern authors
      %p
        If you are a pattern author and wish to update your patterns, please contact the hyph-utf8
        package maintainers through the
        %a{target: "_blank", href: "http://tug.org/mailman/listinfo/tex-hyphen"} tex-hyphen mailing list
        &#x2e;

